
see archive/docs/index.html for more information on the v1 code

The main code for v1 here is pvwatch.py.  It monitors EPICS PVs 
(described in pvlist.xml) and writes files in the local 
WWW server directory.  It can be started and stopped by
the Makefile (for manual control) or the manage.csh script
for automated startup in /etc/init.d or similar.


Another code module, buildSpecPlots.sh, crawls a set of 
subdirectories, looking for SPEC data files and plotting
all scans using defaults (last column vs. first column).


The Python documentation was generated using the commands:
	/APSshare/bin/pydoc -w ./
	mv *.html docs/


Another code module, dirWatch.py, appears to be unused.

